1
00:01:57,239 --> 00:01:57,920
Need a hand?

2
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,280
No, I'm good.

3
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,240
Hold on tight.

4
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,599
Tell me,

5
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,439
why don't I have

6
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:39,199
such a pretty cousin?

7
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:41,919
Ask your aunt.

8
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,719
So many lavender plants.

9
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:52,960
Stop, stop the motor!

10
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,599
I wanna see.

11
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,120
The lavenders are so pretty!

12
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,960
Look at all of them!

13
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,759
This is just gorgeous!

14
00:03:14,759 --> 00:03:15,319
Pretty?

15
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,120
Not really.

16
00:03:21,759 --> 00:03:23,039
I have nothing to say with someone

17
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:24,800
who can't appreciate beauty like you.

18
00:03:27,199 --> 00:03:28,360
You see beauty.

19
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,360
I see detox

20
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,159
and anti-itch.

21
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,719
Make it into oil or tea,

22
00:03:33,039 --> 00:03:34,159
it can calm nerves

23
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,000
and ease anxiety.

24
00:03:36,039 --> 00:03:37,120
Mood killer.

25
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:39,319
I often pass here after work.

26
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,360
Got bored of it.

27
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,759
Thanks.

28
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,120
When you're not at home,

29
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,319
you go to Shunyi to work?

30
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,840
You fix phones,

31
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:07,719
fix computers,

32
00:04:07,879 --> 00:04:08,960
do all kinds of odd jobs.

33
00:04:09,439 --> 00:04:10,560
You must earn a lot.

34
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:12,240
Xuan Island's doing well too, right?

35
00:04:12,639 --> 00:04:13,919
So why is your family so tight?

36
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,159
You seemed well off
in Beijing.

37
00:04:16,759 --> 00:04:18,120
How did you end up in Zhazhating?

38
00:04:22,759 --> 00:04:23,199
Oh, right,

39
00:04:23,639 --> 00:04:24,959
Big G said

40
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,639
your grades were not bad.

41
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:27,800
Why did you drop out?

42
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:32,240
Your dad pulled strings
to send you here.

43
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,399
He probably wants you to stay.

44
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:36,439
So why go abroad?

45
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:43,600
What's wrong with you?

46
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,680
Can't you talk nicely?

47
00:04:47,519 --> 00:04:48,240
When you ask a question,
people has to answer?

48
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,759
You spend money

49
00:04:50,759 --> 00:04:51,560
to hurt others' dignity?

50
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:52,800
That's arrogance.

51
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,040
You're the one who's biased.

52
00:04:58,279 --> 00:05:00,000
I never meant to hurt anyone.

53
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:01,439
Besides, I already apologized

54
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:02,560
for what I said

55
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,600
to your mom that day.

56
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:06,199
If you don't want to answer,

57
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,079
you can just refuse.

58
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,160
Fine.
I refuse.

59
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,079
Had enough?

60
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,120
No.

61
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:37,560
Let's go.

62
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:38,600
Home.

63
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:04,240
Oh, right.

64
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:05,839
I'll fix your computer tonight
and bring it back.

65
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:07,839
From now on,

66
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:08,879
don't hang around Shunyi.

67
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,079
Why?

68
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:14,000
It's a hassle.

69
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,920
Is the computer fixed yet?

70
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:22,199
- Auntie.
- Ye.

71
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,360
Can it be fixed?

72
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,160
Sniper says he can.

73
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:27,639
- Sniper?
- Sniper?

74
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:30,360
Xing Wu.
Mr. Zhao.

75
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:32,800
Sniper?

76
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:37,720
Big G says

77
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,519
the repair will cost a lot.

78
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,279
Take this.

79
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:44,279
No, don't worry about it.

80
00:06:44,839 --> 00:06:45,519
It can be fixed.

81
00:06:46,199 --> 00:06:47,439
Take the money back.

82
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:48,519
She's got money.

83
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,600
I hope it's not a problem.

84
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:51,240
Grandma.
Not at all.

85
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,680
Sniper works fast.

86
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:55,759
Good, good.

87
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,839
Sorry for all the trouble.

88
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:58,759
I feel so sorry.

89
00:06:58,879 --> 00:07:00,240
I bought these sea cucumbers.

90
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,240
Please take them.

91
00:07:01,519 --> 00:07:03,040
Or I won't feel right.

92
00:07:03,519 --> 00:07:04,360
Go on, take them.

93
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,800
Take them.

94
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,279
Fine.

95
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:10,560
I'll take the sea cucumbers.

96
00:07:10,959 --> 00:07:11,839
You keep the money.

97
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,600
OK then.

98
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,160
I'd better get back
and report to my wife.

99
00:07:16,199 --> 00:07:17,079
Go on, go.

100
00:07:17,519 --> 00:07:18,279
Sorry about this.
No worries.

101
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,560
I'd go back.
Bye.

102
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:20,839
Take care.

103
00:07:22,279 --> 00:07:23,079
He's henchpecked.

104
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:24,519
He had to beg his wife for money.

105
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:26,360
Thank you, Ye.

106
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:28,680
Um...

107
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,240
The meal Big G made

108
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,399
for you
is still warm on the stove.

109
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,920
I'm going to the next door.

110
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:34,439
Ok.

111
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:35,560
Eat it yourself.

112
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,120
Why no charge

113
00:07:48,519 --> 00:07:49,120
this time?

114
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:51,879
Sea cucumbers for a computer,

115
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,160
fair trade.

116
00:07:56,199 --> 00:07:57,240
Here, take this.

117
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:00,560
Fix the computer faster.

118
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:01,639
If you want me out of Xuan Island
as soon as possible.

119
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:06,680
You're welcome.

120
00:08:55,279 --> 00:08:56,320
"My love".

121
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,960
That poor girl.

122
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,879
Her mom passed away years ago.

123
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:25,320
If it weren't
for family trouble,

124
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:26,919
her dad probably wouldn't have
sent her here.

125
00:09:36,639 --> 00:09:38,279
That's my boy!

126
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:41,879
Where's the money?

127
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:43,039
Speak up!

128
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,639
Or I'll kill you!

129
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,240
Still silent?

130
00:09:48,519 --> 00:09:49,840
Stop hitting my mom!

131
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,840
You were pregnant with another man's kid

132
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,279
when I married you.

133
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:53,679
Did I ever complain?

134
00:09:54,519 --> 00:09:55,559
Now the business fails,

135
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,399
you've supported me for years,

136
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:59,399
and you look down on me?

137
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:01,080
I'll beat you!

138
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,200
Beat you!

139
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:04,879
Beat you!

140
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:06,440
Let go!
Get off!

141
00:10:07,559 --> 00:10:08,519
Wu!
Are you crazy?

142
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:11,279
How could you hit a child?

143
00:10:13,639 --> 00:10:14,480
Don't cry, don't cry.

144
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,000
Xing Guodong.

145
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,080
Wu.
It's okay.

146
00:10:24,639 --> 00:10:25,360
It's okay.

147
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:30,519
I'm ok.

148
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:05,720
Wu.

149
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:06,799
Tired?

150
00:11:07,679 --> 00:11:08,440
Have some skewers.

151
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:10,759
I bought from Zhang's.

152
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:12,320
His cable box broke.

153
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:13,879
He wants you to fix it.

154
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:14,799
OK.

155
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,120
His son broke his leg on a site.

156
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,960
Don't expect much pay.

157
00:11:20,799 --> 00:11:21,279
Also,

158
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:22,320
Mr. Liu's boat engine
keeps stalling.

159
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,200
He wants you to check it.

160
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,039
Got it.

161
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,279
I'll go tomorrow.

162
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:28,519
OK.

163
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:30,639
Do you know

164
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,120
what's it like falling from the sky

165
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:34,360
into the mud?

166
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,519
I'd have to fly to know.

167
00:12:15,399 --> 00:12:16,720
Just like a swap.

168
00:12:22,399 --> 00:12:23,440
[Proof of funds done.]

169
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:24,320
[All documents ready.]
[Then visa.]

170
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,000
Thanks for saving me, girl.

171
00:12:32,879 --> 00:12:34,799
[All set, except courses.]

172
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:42,919
Grandma?

173
00:12:46,919 --> 00:12:48,120
Grandma, it's okay!

174
00:12:48,159 --> 00:12:48,960
I'm here!

175
00:12:51,039 --> 00:12:51,600
I'm with you.

176
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,000
It's all right.

177
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,559
You're okay now.

178
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,240
Grandma?

179
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:48,720
How is she?

180
00:13:50,519 --> 00:13:51,519
She took her meds

181
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:53,039
and fell asleep.

182
00:13:53,519 --> 00:13:54,000
Good.

183
00:14:02,399 --> 00:14:03,159
Is your hand okay?

184
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:08,440
Fine.

185
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,159
I fixed your computer.

186
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:18,600
Thanks.

187
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,720
Great, everything's still here.

188
00:14:44,919 --> 00:14:45,759
Xing Wu

189
00:14:45,799 --> 00:14:47,120
talks rough

190
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,240
but has skills.

191
00:15:16,639 --> 00:15:17,519
Finally done picking courses.

192
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,000
Congrats.

193
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,279
Big life decision.

194
00:15:25,799 --> 00:15:26,679
Congrats to you too.

195
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:28,919
Soon you'll

196
00:15:28,919 --> 00:15:29,559
get rid of me.

197
00:15:32,519 --> 00:15:33,919
You know yourself well.

198
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,399
I'm happy today,

199
00:15:37,759 --> 00:15:38,720
so I'll let it slide.

200
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:49,039
What?

201
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,639
Treat that cut.

202
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,559
It's hot, might get infected.

203
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,600
Thank you for today.

204
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,519
It was nothing.

205
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,200
Don't mention it.

206
00:16:12,159 --> 00:16:13,159
You seem to know
how to help patients.

207
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:15,240
Yes.

208
00:16:16,399 --> 00:16:17,720
My mom was sick

209
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,879
for a while,

210
00:16:20,039 --> 00:16:20,879
so just in case,

211
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:22,759
I learned

212
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,759
a lot of first aid.

213
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,480
But in the end,

214
00:16:31,519 --> 00:16:32,879
I couldn't save her.

215
00:16:43,679 --> 00:16:44,200
Sorry,

216
00:16:45,279 --> 00:16:46,080
I didn't mean to...

217
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:53,600
It's fine.

218
00:16:54,919 --> 00:16:56,320
Long day. I'm tired.

219
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,120
I'm going to sleep.

220
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:02,759
Good night.

221
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,640
Here it comes.

222
00:18:21,839 --> 00:18:22,920
The last dish.

223
00:18:23,799 --> 00:18:24,559
Auntie,

224
00:18:24,599 --> 00:18:26,039
is it a special day?

225
00:18:28,279 --> 00:18:30,000
Yes, it is.

226
00:18:30,319 --> 00:18:31,160
My fault.

227
00:18:31,519 --> 00:18:33,359
I was busy yesterday.

228
00:18:33,599 --> 00:18:34,680
Grandma said

229
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:36,519
you helped her a lot

230
00:18:37,079 --> 00:18:38,359
and got hurt.

231
00:18:39,519 --> 00:18:41,319
You saved our family.

232
00:18:41,519 --> 00:18:42,519
So I

233
00:18:42,839 --> 00:18:44,119
went early this morning

234
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:46,319
and bought fresh seafood

235
00:18:46,599 --> 00:18:47,519
just to cook for you.

236
00:18:48,079 --> 00:18:49,160
Isn't that too much?

237
00:18:49,519 --> 00:18:50,839
Not at all.

238
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,960
Grandma, are you okay?

239
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:53,720
I'm fine.

240
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,359
Just an old condition.

241
00:18:56,119 --> 00:18:57,599
Thanks to you yesterday.

242
00:18:58,799 --> 00:18:59,799
Look,

243
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,119
you suffered.

244
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:04,519
Wu,

245
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,079
as long as

246
00:19:06,079 --> 00:19:07,119
Ye is here,

247
00:19:07,319 --> 00:19:08,200
you should make sure

248
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,440
that she's comfortable.

249
00:19:09,599 --> 00:19:10,519
Take good care of her,

250
00:19:10,839 --> 00:19:12,279
or I'll hold you responsible.

251
00:19:12,839 --> 00:19:13,720
Don't worry, Grandma.

252
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:19,839
Let's dig!

253
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:21,599
Here.
OK.

254
00:19:23,799 --> 00:19:26,240
A shrimp for our Ye.

255
00:19:27,079 --> 00:19:27,640
Thanks, Auntie.

256
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,079
Fresh squid.

257
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,680
Lanfang makes it the best.

258
00:19:31,559 --> 00:19:31,960
OK.

259
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,000
This dish is great.

260
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,759
Some soup for you.

261
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,680
You're installing an AC for me?

262
00:20:01,559 --> 00:20:02,759
A used one from the shop.

263
00:20:02,839 --> 00:20:03,440
Use it for now.

264
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,720
It's not just a used AC.

265
00:20:08,079 --> 00:20:10,160
It's a lifestyle upgrade.

266
00:20:59,799 --> 00:21:00,440
Does your hand still hurt?

267
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,319
Much better.

268
00:21:35,119 --> 00:21:36,759
How long has Grandma been sick?

269
00:21:37,559 --> 00:21:38,599
Two years.

270
00:21:39,119 --> 00:21:39,839
Not just epilepsy.

271
00:21:40,279 --> 00:21:41,400
Her paralysis is also worse.

272
00:21:42,359 --> 00:21:43,319
Sometimes she loses her memory.

273
00:21:44,039 --> 00:21:44,759
Brain diseases can have

274
00:21:45,359 --> 00:21:47,640
all kinds of sudden symptoms.

275
00:21:48,039 --> 00:21:48,720
So

276
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:50,680
you come back

277
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,519
every day to watch her eat,

278
00:21:53,119 --> 00:21:54,079
in case something happens?

279
00:21:55,359 --> 00:21:56,720
Li Lanfang has no patience.

280
00:21:57,119 --> 00:21:58,519
She often forgets to cook.

281
00:21:58,759 --> 00:21:59,599
So I have to keep an eye.

282
00:22:02,039 --> 00:22:04,079
You take good care of her.

283
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,680
She raised me.

284
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,079
Without her, I'd be nothing.

285
00:22:11,359 --> 00:22:12,400
You're amazing.

286
00:22:13,039 --> 00:22:14,519
We're about the same age,

287
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:15,960
and you're the man of the house.

288
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,160
But what about your dad?

289
00:22:20,079 --> 00:22:21,039
Never seen him.

290
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:24,720
Dead.

291
00:22:27,759 --> 00:22:29,200
But I heard

292
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,400
he left town.

293
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:31,680
Gone so long,

294
00:22:32,680 --> 00:22:33,599
deep in debt.

295
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,079
Might as well be dead.

296
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:57,440
Done.

297
00:23:03,039 --> 00:23:04,160
So comfortable.

298
00:23:04,519 --> 00:23:05,640
All I need now is

299
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:06,839
half a chilled watermelon.

300
00:23:06,839 --> 00:23:07,759
It'd be perfect.

301
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:10,160
Here.

302
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:12,359
You really have.

303
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,200
Why are you being so nice?

304
00:23:17,799 --> 00:23:19,720
An AC, watermelon...

305
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,319
Not just repaying a favor?

306
00:23:22,839 --> 00:23:23,680
Or do you want my final payment?

307
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:26,519
Don't want? I'll take it back.
No, no.

308
00:23:27,559 --> 00:23:28,319
I'll eat.

309
00:23:36,839 --> 00:23:37,880
So sweet!

310
00:23:39,119 --> 00:23:40,759
This is how summer should be.

311
00:23:42,119 --> 00:23:42,759
Honestly,

312
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:44,319
before I came to Zhazhating,

313
00:23:44,319 --> 00:23:45,039
I didn't know

314
00:23:45,559 --> 00:23:47,200
summers by the sea could be this hot.

315
00:23:49,079 --> 00:23:50,079
So

316
00:23:50,119 --> 00:23:51,279
how did you spend summers?

317
00:23:52,319 --> 00:23:53,079
Normally.

318
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:55,720
You mean

319
00:23:55,799 --> 00:23:57,039
our summers aren't normal?

320
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,759
No, that's not what I meant.

321
00:24:00,359 --> 00:24:01,839
I meant I never

322
00:24:01,839 --> 00:24:02,960
felt the heat.

323
00:24:03,319 --> 00:24:04,559
Everywhere was cool.

324
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:06,759
Home had a ventilation system,

325
00:24:06,839 --> 00:24:08,000
malls had AC.

326
00:24:09,759 --> 00:24:10,599
You never went out?

327
00:24:11,559 --> 00:24:12,400
I had a driver.

328
00:24:13,119 --> 00:24:14,839
If it got too hot, I'd go abroad

329
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:16,359
to somewhere cooler.

330
00:24:17,519 --> 00:24:18,079
But

331
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:19,960
most of the time,

332
00:24:20,519 --> 00:24:21,279
I stayed home

333
00:24:21,279 --> 00:24:22,519
with a tutor.

334
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,960
Sounds nice.

335
00:24:26,559 --> 00:24:27,160
It was okay.
What about you?

336
00:24:28,519 --> 00:24:28,960
Me?

337
00:24:30,759 --> 00:24:31,519
Simple.

338
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,000
Run between Xuan Island and Shunyi.

339
00:24:34,119 --> 00:24:34,759
Work if there's work.

340
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:36,559
If it's too hot,

341
00:24:36,759 --> 00:24:37,759
go swimming

342
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,359
with Kyle and Big G.

343
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:42,640
Pretty wild.

344
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,319
But tough.

345
00:24:49,359 --> 00:24:50,799
It must have been hard for you

346
00:24:51,319 --> 00:24:52,400
coming from Beijing to Zhazhating.

347
00:25:05,039 --> 00:25:05,599
But

348
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:08,000
today,

349
00:25:08,799 --> 00:25:10,519
for the first time since I got here,

350
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:12,880
I don't feel

351
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:14,920
so miserable.

352
00:25:17,519 --> 00:25:18,640
Because of this used AC?

353
00:25:21,319 --> 00:25:22,440
Not just the AC.

354
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,640
The new lock,

355
00:25:26,279 --> 00:25:26,920
the showerhead,

356
00:25:28,519 --> 00:25:29,680
the watermelon,

357
00:25:30,119 --> 00:25:31,440
and you fixing my computer.

358
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:38,640
And...

359
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:58,200
I'm going.

360
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,039
And thank you

361
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,279
for making this summer in Zhazhating

362
00:26:08,279 --> 00:26:09,400
less desperate.

363
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,720
Who's so shameless

364
00:27:14,079 --> 00:27:15,319
to steal clothes?

365
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:18,200
Which lowlife

366
00:27:18,599 --> 00:27:20,279
stole a girl's clothes?

367
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:23,759
That desperate?

368
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,279
No decency!

369
00:27:29,119 --> 00:27:30,640
After a few pieces of cloth?

370
00:27:30,839 --> 00:27:31,880
Are you even human?

371
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,519
What's wrong, Auntie?

372
00:27:33,519 --> 00:27:34,440
Early in the morning...

373
00:27:35,319 --> 00:27:36,559
Your clothes...

374
00:27:36,559 --> 00:27:38,160
Your clothes got stolen.

375
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,119
I didn't wash any.

376
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,519
I did.

377
00:27:41,519 --> 00:27:42,200
I saw your clothes
there yesterday

378
00:27:42,799 --> 00:27:44,039
and washed them.

379
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:44,920
My fault.
It's my bad.

380
00:27:45,839 --> 00:27:46,680
If I hadn't,

381
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,039
this wouldn't have happened.

382
00:27:49,039 --> 00:27:50,039
You didn't mean to.

383
00:27:50,839 --> 00:27:53,079
But your bra

384
00:27:53,599 --> 00:27:54,559
is gone.

385
00:27:56,039 --> 00:27:57,000
Maybe a mistake?

386
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,880
Who'd steal bra?

387
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:00,920
In Zhazhating,

388
00:28:01,319 --> 00:28:02,519
let alone bra.

389
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,000
Even the copper wire

390
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,119
off poles.

391
00:28:06,519 --> 00:28:08,039
Someone'll take it.

392
00:28:09,079 --> 00:28:10,640
Give the clothes back! Now!

393
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:12,839
What's all this?

394
00:28:12,839 --> 00:28:14,200
You two going at it

395
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:14,920
this early?

396
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,079
Solving a mystery?

397
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:19,880
Catch the thief yet?

398
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:20,799
Not yet.

399
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,599
Still looking.

400
00:28:23,519 --> 00:28:24,920
This yard

401
00:28:25,559 --> 00:28:26,759
is so small.

402
00:28:27,119 --> 00:28:29,160
Just a few families.

403
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:31,640
Everyone knows who's sneaky.

404
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,960
We all know.

405
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:34,960
I hung clothes yesterday.

406
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,839
Did you see anything?

407
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:40,839
I've been swamped,

408
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:42,000
run off my feet.

409
00:28:42,559 --> 00:28:43,240
What did you say?

410
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,359
Your clothes are missing?

411
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:45,720
I didn't see.

412
00:28:47,319 --> 00:28:48,200
Didn't see anything.

413
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:50,640
Didn't see? Then why ask?

414
00:28:51,319 --> 00:28:52,680
Who took them, bring them back.

415
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,200
What happened?

416
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,599
What's wrong with you people?

417
00:28:55,599 --> 00:28:56,559
You steal everything!
Computers, bra.

418
00:28:57,759 --> 00:28:58,519
Wearing someone else's bra?
Isn't that gross?

419
00:28:59,839 --> 00:29:00,519
Zhazhating and I

420
00:29:00,519 --> 00:29:01,559
just don't mix.

421
00:29:01,559 --> 00:29:02,599
So annoying!

422
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,079
Was it hanging here?

423
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,720
I left it here last night,

424
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:11,799
and it's gone this morning.

425
00:29:14,759 --> 00:29:15,880
Annoying.

426
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:07,000
Good?

427
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:08,519
Yeah.

428
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,319
Want a piece, Wu?

429
00:30:10,799 --> 00:30:11,599
Where are Qing Ye's clothes?

430
00:30:12,799 --> 00:30:13,519
I didn't steal them.

431
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,039
Did I say you did?

432
00:30:15,519 --> 00:30:15,880
I...

433
00:30:20,599 --> 00:30:21,119
What?

434
00:30:22,119 --> 00:30:23,160
What about the footprints

435
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:23,839
under the clothesline?

436
00:30:24,799 --> 00:30:25,599
Footprints.

437
00:30:26,279 --> 00:30:26,880
They're everywhere.

438
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,039
That's from hanging clothes.

439
00:30:28,359 --> 00:30:29,160
What's that got to do with me?

440
00:30:32,920 --> 00:30:33,640
Xing Wu.

441
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:35,119
I tell you.

442
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,400
Don't push it.

443
00:30:36,519 --> 00:30:37,599
I have a temper too.

444
00:30:37,599 --> 00:30:38,119
Got it?

445
00:30:39,119 --> 00:30:39,920
Wu, Wu, Wu.

446
00:30:40,039 --> 00:30:41,119
You stole the computer too. Right?

447
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:41,839
Not me.
I wouldn't dare.

448
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,640
I might take wire,

449
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:44,799
but not a computer.

450
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:47,519
What?

451
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:49,359
Wu.

452
00:30:49,519 --> 00:30:51,119
Hot, hot, hot!

453
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:53,079
My face! Wu.

454
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:54,519
I'm sorry, Wu.

455
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:55,279
I'm sorry!

456
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:56,960
Wu Laoer,

457
00:30:57,799 --> 00:30:58,440
listen up.

458
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:00,079
Don't you dare eye Qing Ye.

459
00:31:00,599 --> 00:31:01,359
Or next time,

460
00:31:01,759 --> 00:31:03,000
I'll send you to the King of Hell.

461
00:31:03,079 --> 00:31:04,160
OK, OK, Wu.

462
00:31:04,319 --> 00:31:05,599
I promise. I promise!

463
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:22,880
What are you looking at?

464
00:31:23,759 --> 00:31:25,000
Never seen picking up shoes?

465
00:31:26,799 --> 00:31:28,599
Come in, come in.

466
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,519
Pick whatever you want.

467
00:31:35,559 --> 00:31:37,200
Wear what you like.

468
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:38,759
These are all
my prized clothes.

469
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:41,799
No need, Auntie.

470
00:31:42,119 --> 00:31:43,680
I only lost one bra.

471
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,359
You don't have to lend me yours.

472
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:48,599
I see you only have

473
00:31:48,599 --> 00:31:49,920
a few outfits.

474
00:31:50,359 --> 00:31:52,079
Did you not bring enough?

475
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,680
Don't worry,

476
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,079
My clothes are pretty.

477
00:31:57,359 --> 00:31:58,400
I learned fashion

478
00:31:58,400 --> 00:31:59,599
from your mom.

479
00:32:01,839 --> 00:32:03,240
This was the trend

480
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:04,279
when I was young.

481
00:32:04,759 --> 00:32:05,559
Pretty, right?

482
00:32:06,039 --> 00:32:06,559
Try it.

483
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,000
Me? No, no, no.

484
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,319
Try it, try it.

485
00:32:09,319 --> 00:32:09,920
- No.
- Try it.

486
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,119
Come on, it's cute.

487
00:32:11,319 --> 00:32:12,759
Trust me.

488
00:32:12,839 --> 00:32:14,119
It looks good.

489
00:32:15,039 --> 00:32:17,599
Come out, it's fine.

490
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:18,680
Come on, come out.

491
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:20,039
Wu,

492
00:32:20,759 --> 00:32:21,680
where have you been?

493
00:32:22,519 --> 00:32:23,240
Working out.

494
00:32:23,759 --> 00:32:24,559
Perfect timing.

495
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:25,519
Um...

496
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:27,400
Ye's a bit shy.

497
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:28,920
You can help us decide.

498
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:30,279
What do you mean?

499
00:32:32,279 --> 00:32:33,279
Just come out.
Come on, come out.

500
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,640
My clothes look great.

501
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,079
Well? Good?

502
00:32:39,359 --> 00:32:40,119
What are you laughing at?

503
00:32:40,119 --> 00:32:41,559
You don't have to speak.

504
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,279
I'll stay silent.

505
00:32:46,359 --> 00:32:46,799
Change.

506
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:47,920
Let's change.

507
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,839
We'll find the one you like.

508
00:32:50,119 --> 00:32:50,519
Let's go.
These are

509
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,079
my favorite clothes I rarely wear.

510
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:55,440
Xing Wu.

511
00:32:57,799 --> 00:32:58,359
Look at this.
How is it?

512
00:33:07,519 --> 00:33:07,880
Got it.
Change again.

513
00:33:09,319 --> 00:33:09,720
Let's go.

514
00:33:31,799 --> 00:33:32,400
Maybe

515
00:33:32,839 --> 00:33:34,039
I should pick for myself.

516
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:35,720
OK.

517
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:36,960
Pick what you like.
Anything.

518
00:33:45,319 --> 00:33:46,200
Doesn't look good?

519
00:34:18,599 --> 00:34:19,840
What do you think, Auntie?

520
00:34:21,519 --> 00:34:23,519
Just like your mom back in the day.

521
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:28,760
Such long legs.

522
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:30,639
Beautiful.

523
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:38,239
Mom.
Come here.

524
00:34:43,599 --> 00:34:44,119
What?

525
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:45,599
Later,

526
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:47,000
go buy Qing Ye

527
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:47,800
two outfits.

528
00:34:48,559 --> 00:34:49,320
I'm busy.

529
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,599
Play less mahjong,

530
00:34:50,599 --> 00:34:51,320
and you'll have time.

531
00:34:51,599 --> 00:34:54,159
Zhao Pock's son is getting married tomorrow.

532
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:54,880
Tonight is

533
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:55,920
the pre-wedding feast.

534
00:34:56,039 --> 00:34:57,280
I promised Big G's mom,

535
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:57,880
Kyle's mom,
I'd go help.

536
00:34:58,719 --> 00:35:00,039
I have to go soon.

537
00:35:01,519 --> 00:35:01,920
In a hurry?

538
00:35:03,119 --> 00:35:03,559
Very.
See?

539
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:05,360
They're already calling.

540
00:35:08,679 --> 00:35:09,920
Just let her wear mine.

541
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,159
Then who'll buy for her?

542
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:12,679
You figure it out.

543
00:35:13,679 --> 00:35:15,440
I'll take Grandma over.

544
00:35:15,719 --> 00:35:16,280
Later,
you bring Ye.

545
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:19,760
We paid for the feast.

546
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:20,519
So eat our money's worth.

547
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:21,400
Here we go again.

548
00:35:25,199 --> 00:35:27,559
Hold the sky with both hands.

549
00:35:29,239 --> 00:35:30,440
Press up.

550
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,360
Down.

551
00:35:39,719 --> 00:35:40,880
You know Baduanjin?

552
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:44,119
Started three minutes ago.

553
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,519
I'm going to the county to shop.

554
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:50,400
Wanna come?

555
00:35:51,519 --> 00:35:52,039
No.

556
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,760
First my computer,

557
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:55,519
then my clothes.
I think

558
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,320
before I leave,

559
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:00,599
I'll just practice turtle breathing

560
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:01,760
and stay calm.

561
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:04,719
Fine.
I'm off.

562
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:06,719
Wait.

563
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:09,880
Can you...

564
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,639
Um...

565
00:36:12,639 --> 00:36:14,280
get me something...

566
00:36:19,679 --> 00:36:21,039
to wear inside?

567
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:22,039
You know?

568
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,360
One-size type.

569
00:36:26,719 --> 00:36:27,159
OK.

570
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:01,360
Hello?
[Wu,]

571
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:02,920
[got a job.]
[Come to Shunyi.]

572
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,719
Are you spying on me?

573
00:37:06,679 --> 00:37:07,400
[What do you mean?]
Nothing.

574
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:09,440
I'll be right there.

575
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:12,280
My sister found you the job.

576
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:15,920
Isn't she in Hainan?

577
00:37:16,639 --> 00:37:17,719
She knows you need money.

578
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:18,920
She's always looking out for you.

579
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:20,320
She treats you

580
00:37:20,679 --> 00:37:21,679
better than me,

581
00:37:21,719 --> 00:37:22,320
her own brother.

582
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:24,360
Stop joking. What's the job?

583
00:37:25,119 --> 00:37:26,119
What's the deal?

584
00:37:26,519 --> 00:37:27,639
Her boss, Mr. Ye,

585
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,039
wants a model plane for his son's competition.

586
00:37:30,719 --> 00:37:31,679
Needs someone to build it.

587
00:37:31,880 --> 00:37:33,159
She recommended you.

588
00:37:33,679 --> 00:37:34,719
Gas-powered.

589
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,039
But I only know a little
about that.

590
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:43,719
What model plane
can't you make?

591
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,320
One thing leads to another.

592
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:48,239
It can't be that hard.

593
00:37:49,719 --> 00:37:50,880
I lack theory.

594
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:52,679
Keeping it light

595
00:37:52,679 --> 00:37:53,360
and agile

596
00:37:54,199 --> 00:37:54,840
